https://codeshare.io/GAOQLe


✅ Step 1 — Install Python 3.10 on Mac

Option A — Homebrew (recommended)

If Homebrew is installed:

brew install python@3.10


This will install Python 3.10 and a python3.10 binary.

Check it:

python3.10 --version
# should print something like Python 3.10.13


Option B — Download installer from python.org

Go to: https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-31013/

Download the macOS installer (x86_64 or universal2)

Install it normally

Open terminal and verify:

python3.10 --version

✅ Step 2 — Create a Python 3.10 virtual environment

In terminal, in your project folder:

python3.10 -m venv myenv


myenv is the environment name

This creates a clean isolated Python environment

✅ Step 3 — Activate the virtual environment
source myenv/bin/activate


Your terminal should now show:

(myenv) user@MacBook …

✅ Step 4 — Upgrade pip (optional but recommended)
pip install --upgrade pip

✅ Step 5 — Install correct packages
pip install numpy opencv-python
pip install tensorflow==2.14.0
pip install mediapipe==0.10.9


This combination works with Python 3.10 and avoids all the protobuf / runtime_version errors.

✅ Step 6 — Test MediaPipe
python -c "import mediapipe as mp; print(dir(mp.solutions))"


You should see hands, pose, holistic, etc. → no errors.

✅ Step 7 — Run your hand gesture script
python hand_gesture_live.py


Live camera feed

Hand landmarks

Gesture labels
